Speaking in Harare soon after the launch of the Amnesty International report in Botswana on the death penalty, Amnesty International applauded President Emerson Mnangagwa for recently commuting death sentences to life. 
While progress has been noted in some countries towards abolishing the death penalty, the report is calling on the total abolishment of the act. 
Thursday's report is called, 'Death Penalty: Sub-Saharan Africa a beacon of hope as global executions and death sentences slide.' More from our Correspondent Simon Muchemwa...
